==English==

===Etymology===
French ''[[naïve]]'', from Latin ''[[nativus]]'' 'native, natural'.

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]]:/naɪiv/

===Adjective===
'''naive'''
# Lacking [[experience]], [[wisdom]], or [[judgement]].
# (of art) Produced in a simple, childlike style, deliberately rejecting sophisticated techniques.
# (of philosophy) Purposefully deluding oneself into believing in innocence and the ability to change things for the better,despite overwhelming proof to the contrary, in order to live a life of hope